ren2 bu4 zhi1 gui3 bu4 jue2

sentences.english: Unconsciously, and Buck Street, has been dealing with for nearly 2 years more.
sentences.chinese: 不知不觉中，和布客街已经打交道了快2年多了。

sentences.english: Dick found himself walking in the direction of the church.
sentences.chinese: 迪克发现自己不知不觉朝教堂方向走去。

sentences.english: Slowly insidiously the fog of the everyday has returned to enshroud me.
sentences.chinese: 慢慢地，不知不觉地，日常的迷雾又回来笼罩了我。

sentences.english: In the most lofty devotion we become unconscious of self.
sentences.chinese: 在最崇高的灵修中，我们变得浑然不觉自我。

sentences.english: I unawares fall in the dream net.
sentences.chinese: 我不知不觉掉进了梦网。

sentences.english: The thief slipped out of the room without anybody noticing.
sentences.chinese: 这个贼神不知鬼不觉地从房间里溜了出来。

sentences.english: Or ever I was aware, my soul made me like the chariots of Amminadib.
sentences.chinese: 不知不觉，我的心将我安置在我尊长的车中。

sentences.english: And the next thing I know, I am on the ground harvesting chanterelles.
sentences.chinese: 不知不觉的，我又在地上捡酒杯蘑菇了。

sentences.english: Tom presently began to drift insensibly back into the concerns of this life again.
sentences.chinese: 不久，汤姆不知不觉地关心起眼前的现实来。

sentences.english: Rip currents are so strong that they can carry swimmers away from shore before they know what's happening.
sentences.chinese: 强流来势凶猛，会在不知不觉问把游泳者卷走。

sentences.english: We have thus imperceptibly climb to the top of the hill, the temple is still made a wish.
sentences.chinese: 就这样我们不知不觉爬到山顶，还在庙里许了愿。

sentences.english: Without deliberately thinking about it, MOTIFS for love-lyrics began to agitate his brain.
sentences.chinese: 爱情抒怀诗的主题不知不觉已开始在他脑子里活跃。

sentences.english: My wet eyes felt warm in the brisk autumn wind.
sentences.chinese: 我的眼睛不觉在秋季清朗的风中湿润发热。

sentences.english: They were frightened but did not feel any pain at first.
sentences.chinese: 起初他们只感到惊怕，并不觉痛。

sentences.english: He had insidiously wormed his way into her affections.
sentences.chinese: 他已经神不知鬼不觉的逐渐赢得了她的爱情。

sentences.english: They had mysteriously found their way there from the wine cellar!
sentences.chinese: 这些酒瓶神不知鬼不觉地从酒窖离开了这里。

definition: in a flash/in the blink of an eye/to glance
